<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:The code contains a code block that is unreachable due to a condition that can never be true. Specifically, the 'if (NULL == response->crc)' block under the 'else' clause is marked with a comment 'There is no way to reach this code', indicating that this block is unreachable because the logic guarantees response->crc must not be NULL in that path. This violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.1 which forbids unreachable code.
</scenario>
